          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>If a product within the basket has expired, is no longer in stock or has exceeded the quantity allowed, the product is removed from the basket and a message is displayed informing the user that the product has been removed due to (whatever the sceanrio for it's removal).</p>
            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There is only a single layout mode for this component.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <p>The Order error replicates the product item components from the <a href="basket-product.html">Basket</a> and <a href="checkout-product.html">Checkout</a> pages where further details about the CSS for these components can be found</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/order-error.scss</p>
            <p>/large-components/order-error.scss</p>
            <p>/small-components/order-error.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>There are several error states for a product whilst moving through the checkout process. The item may longer be available by the time the user clicks proceed. The product alert error is flexible and can hold any message against a product item. Several variants are shown as illustration.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Post delivery amendments</h3>
            <p>A product alert panel has been added to the top of the page if a voucher summary change is required to anchor users to the voucher summary section.</p>
            <p><em>see figure 1 below</em></p>
            <p class="styleguide-img">
              <img src="../img/styleguide/product-alert.png" alt="illustration of product alert message">
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
